# rh.lean тАФ Phases CXXXтАУCXXXI: the overflow-residue engine and its polynomial instantiation

The decisive operator of overflow calculus is the logarithmic derivative
  ╬Ы[f](z) := f'(z) / f(z).
For a factored object it expands as a signed residue cloud
  ╬Ы[f](z) = ╬г_j m_j / (z тИТ r_j) тИТ ╬г_k n_k / (z тИТ p_k).
Real-rooted clouds satisfy the **anti-Herglotz** upper-half-plane sign law
  Im R(z) тЙд 0  for  Im z > 0,
since `Im 1/(z тИТ r) = тИТ(Im z)/|z тИТ r|┬▓ тЙд 0` for `r тИИ тДЭ`. A nonreal
upper-half-plane zero of `f` would force `╬Ы[f]` to escape upward there
(probe `╧Б тИТ ╬╡┬╖I`), contradicting the law.

This file lands the **engine** (CXXX abstract layer) and its **polynomial
instantiation** (CXXXI). The active proof shape is:

  AntiHerglotz ╬Ы[╬Ю]  +  pole-witness on ╬Ы[╬Ю]
                     тЗТ  no upper-half-plane zeros of ╬Ю
  +  ╬Ю(z╠Д) = conj ╬Ю(z)
                     тЗТ  every zero of ╬Ю is real.

For polynomials this is fully proved end-to-end in ┬з7. For an abstract
target `╬Ю` it is fully proved in ┬з8 modulo three honest hypotheses.

