/-- тнР **PROVED тАФ top-level closure on `[10, 140]`.** Given the 9 slab
certificates, for any probe `(z, T)` in the band with the adaptive
constraint, the closed-form S-error bound (at the appropriate per-slab
`(C, D)`) is dominated by `тИТIm(model z)`.

The witness `(C, D)` is read off from whichever slab covers `T`.
Combined with the analytic CLV/CLVII chain for `T тЙе 140` and a future
`FirstZeroBandCertificate` instance for `[2╧А, 10]`, this gives the
unconditional `hclosed` chain on the entire admissible band. -/
theorem hclosed_on_10_140
    (model : тДВ тЖТ тДВ)
    (cert_10_12 : тИА z : тДВ, тИА T : тДЭ, 10 тЙд T тЖТ T тЙд 12 тЖТ 0 < z.im тЖТ
        2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) тЙд T тЖТ
        closedFormSErrorBoundCD 0 (21/100 : тДЭ) z.im T тЙд -(model z).im)
    (cert_12_13 : тИА z : тДВ, тИА T : тДЭ, 12 тЙд T тЖТ T тЙд 13 тЖТ 0 < z.im тЖТ
        2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) тЙд T тЖТ
        closedFormSErrorBoundCD 0 (31/100 : тДЭ) z.im T тЙд -(model z).im)
    (cert_13_14 : тИА z : тДВ, тИА T : тДЭ, 13 тЙд T тЖТ T тЙд 14 тЖТ 0 < z.im тЖТ
        2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) тЙд T тЖТ
        closedFormSErrorBoundCD 0 (44/100 : тДЭ) z.im T тЙд -(model z).im)
    (cert_14_19 : тИА z : тДВ, тИА T : тДЭ, 14 тЙд T тЖТ T тЙд 19 тЖТ 0 < z.im тЖТ
        2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) тЙд T тЖТ
