/-- ЁЯМЯЁЯМЯ **PROVED тАФ `XiLowResidualMargin` from guarded explicit data + arith
margin.** This is the key bridge: the OUTPUT `XiLowResidualMargin` is
unguarded, which is fine because at zeros the totalization automatically
gives equality `|Im(error)| = -Im(model)` via
`errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp`. The INPUT explicit-data
hypothesis only needs to hold at non-zero `z`, where the analytic
discharge actually works. -/
theorem XiLowResidualMargin_of_explicitAtAwayFromZeros_and_marginAt
    {T gamma1 D : тДЭ}
    (Hexplicit : XiLowResidualExplicitDataAtAwayFromZeros T gamma1 D
                    honestZeroDensityModelTwoPi)
    (Hmargin : LowMarginDominatesExplicitBoundAt T gamma1 D
                  honestZeroDensityModelTwoPi) :
    XiLowResidualMargin honestZeroDensityModelTwoPi := by
  intro z hz
  by_cases hzero : XiPullback z = 0
  ┬╖ exact errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp
      (hmodelAnti_of_honestZeroDensityModel
